Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of finding a minimum cardinality perfect edge dominating set in graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorics. The paper discusses the complexity of the problem and provides both hardness and solvability results for different classes of graphs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
